  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2015-02-26T05:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Encouraging Employee Ownership Act\n\nDirects the Securities and Exchange Commission to revise regulations to require an issuer to furnish investors with additional specified disclosures regarding compensatory benefit plans if the aggregate sales price or amount of securities sold during any consecutive 12-month period exceeds $10 million (currently $5 million), indexed for inflation every five years."
